## Implementation Steps (9 Phases)

### **Phase 1: Project Setup & Core Infrastructure** (Days 1-2)

1. Initialize Node.js project with Express
   - `npm init`, install dependencies (express, mongoose, dotenv, bcryptjs, jsonwebtoken, cors)
2. Set up folder structure: `models/`, `routes/`, `controllers/`, `middleware/`, `utils/`, `config/`
3. Connect to MongoDB (local or Atlas)
4. Create environment configuration (.env)
5. Set up error handling middleware
6. Set up CORS and request logging middleware

### **Phase 2: Authentication & User Management** (Days 2-3)

1. Create User model (email, password, role, profile data)
2. Implement password hashing (bcryptjs)
3. Create JWT authentication middleware
4. Build auth routes:
   - POST `/auth/register`
   - POST `/auth/login`
   - POST `/auth/forgot-password`
   - POST `/auth/reset-password`
5. Create user routes:
   - GET `/users/profile`
   - PUT `/users/profile`
   - GET `/users/{id}` (admin)

### **Phase 3: Product & Category Management** (Days 3-4)

1. Create Product model (name, description, price, category, stock, images, ratings, reviews)
2. Create Category model (name, description)
3. Build product routes:
   - POST `/products` (admin only)
   - GET `/products` (with pagination & filtering and search)
   - GET `/products/{id}`
   - PUT `/products/{id}` (admin only) (upadate product)
   - DELETE `/products/{id}` (admin only) (delte product)
4. Build category routes (CRUD, admin only)
5. Implement search/filter logic

### **Phase 4: Shopping Cart** (Day 4)

1. Create Cart model (userId, items[], createdAt, updatedAt)
2. Build cart routes:
   - POST `/cart/add`
   - DELETE `/cart/items/{productId}`
   - PUT `/cart/items/{productId}`
   - GET `/cart`
   - POST `/cart/clear`
3. Implement cart calculation (subtotal, tax, shipping)

### **Phase 5: Orders & Checkout** (Days 5-6)

1. Create Order model (userId, items[], status, totalPrice, shippingAddress, paymentMethod, createdAt)
2. Build checkout logic:
   - Validate inventory before creating order
   - Calculate final price with shipping address
3. Build order routes:
   - POST `/orders` (create order from cart)
   - GET `/orders` (user's order history)
   - GET `/orders/{id}`
   - GET `/admin/orders` (admin view all)
   - PUT `/admin/orders/{id}/status`
4. Implement inventory reduction on order creation

### **Phase 6: Payment Processing** (Days 6-7)

1. Create Payment model (orderId, transactionId, method, status, amount, createdAt)
2. Implement payment routes:
   - POST `/payments/create-intent` (Stripe payment intent)
   - POST `/payments/confirm`
   - Webhook to handle payment callbacks
3. Link payment to order (mark order as paid)

### **Phase 7: Reviews, Ratings & Admin Analytics** (Days 7-8)

1. Create Review model (productId, userId, rating, comment, createdAt)
2. Build review routes:
   - POST `/products/{id}/reviews`
   - GET `/products/{id}/reviews`
   - DELETE `/reviews/{id}`
3. Update product model with avg rating calculation
4. Build admin analytics routes:
   - GET `/admin/analytics/revenue`
   - GET `/admin/analytics/users`
   - GET `/admin/analytics/inventory`

### **Phase 8: Notifications (Email)** (Days 8-9)

1. Set up email service (Nodemailer + Gmail)
2. Create email templates (order confirmation, shipment, password reset)
3. Implement email triggers:
   - On successful registration
   - On successful payment
   - On order shipment
   - On password reset request

### **Phase 9: Testing, Validation & Deployment** (Days 9-10)

1. Test all endpoints (Postman)
2. Add input validation & error handling
3. Add request rate limiting (express-rate-limit)
4. Add logging (morgan)
5. Set up environment-specific configs
6. Deploy to Heroku/Railway

