Phase 4: Shopping Cart with Variants & Guest Merge (Day 4)

Shopping cart stores items with up to two optional variant options (e.g., Size and Color, both optional). Each item tracks quantity, priceAtAdd (for detecting price changes), and selectedOptions (option1Name/Value and option2Name/Value, both can be empty). Guest users store cart in browser localStorage before creating an account. Upon login, frontend sends localStorage cart to POST /api/cart/merge endpoint, which validates products, checks for duplicate product+variant combinations, merges quantities if same item exists, and saves final cart to user's database Cart model. After merge, localStorage is cleared and subsequent logins load cart from database. Cart APIs: GET /api/cart, POST /api/cart/add, PUT /api/cart/item/:id, DELETE /api/cart/item/:id, POST /api/cart/merge, POST /api/cart/clear. Price update detection shows "Price updated" if priceAtAdd differs from current product price at checkout.

